The paper deals with the problem of distributed Kalman filtering in a network of interconnected subsystems with distributed control protocols. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also proposes a distributed Kalman filtering scheme for linear time-invariant subsystems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Mathematical Aspects of Control (cs.MA) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Networked and Distributed Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that exploits the particular structure of the considered network, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with estimation and convergence, which suggests that it could also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
